\subsubsection{Provided Bag Data}\label{provided-bag-data}}

\begin{longtable}[]{@{}llll@{}}
\toprule\noalign{}
Topic & Message Type & Rate & Description \\
\midrule\noalign{}
\endhead
\bottomrule\noalign{}
\endlastfoot
\texttt{/imu} & sensor\_msgs/Imu & 1000 Hz & Raw accelerometer and gyroscope data \\
\texttt{/desired\_attitude} & geometry\_msgs/QuaternionStamped & 100 Hz & Target attitude from position controller \\
\texttt{/motor\_commands} & std\_msgs/Float32MultiArray & 100 Hz & Motor speed commands (4 motors) \\
\texttt{/ground\_truth\_pose} & geometry\_msgs/PoseStamped & 100 Hz & Ground truth pose from motion capture \\
\end{longtable}

\hypertarget{deliverables}{%
\subsubsection{Deliverables}\label{deliverables}}

\begin{itemize}
\tightlist
\item
  A complementary filter for attitude estimation fusing gyroscope and accelerometer data
\item
  A cascaded PID attitude controller (rate loop + angle loop) as a ROS2 node
\item
  Motor mixing matrix implementation converting thrust/torque to individual motor speeds
\item
  Implementation of at least two alternative controllers (e.g., LQR, MPC, SMC) for comparison
\item
  A quantitative comparison: attitude RMSE, computation time, and wind disturbance rejection
\end{itemize}

\hypertarget{evaluation-criteria}{%
\subsubsection{Evaluation Criteria}\label{evaluation-criteria}}

\begin{itemize}
\tightlist
\item
  \textbf{Attitude Representation:} Correct quaternion handling, gimbal-lock awareness, rotation math
\item
  \textbf{Control Architecture:} Proper cascaded loop design with appropriate loop rates
\item
  \textbf{Real-Time Awareness:} Computational efficiency, memory allocation strategy, timing considerations
\item
  \textbf{Communication:} Ability to explain cascaded control design and trade-offs during the follow-up interview
\end{itemize}

\hypertarget{skills-you-will-demonstrate}{%
\subsection{Skills You Will Demonstrate}\label{skills-you-will-demonstrate}}

By the end of this session you will be able to:

\begin{itemize}
\tightlist
\item
  Represent quadrotor orientation using quaternions and convert between Euler angles and quaternion representations in ROS2 messages
\item
  Derive the Newton-Euler translational and rotational dynamics of a rigid-body quadrotor from first principles
\item
  Design a cascaded control architecture (position → attitude → rate → motors) and explain why each loop runs at a different frequency
\item
  Implement a PID attitude controller as a ROS2 node that subscribes to IMU data and publishes motor commands
\item
  Map all seven control strategies (CTC, MPC, Adaptive, Robust, Backstepping, SMC, LQR) to the quadrotor plant and implement them as interchangeable ROS2 nodes
\item
  Construct and invert the motor mixing matrix to convert desired thrust and torques into individual motor speeds
\item
  Implement a complementary filter for attitude estimation by fusing gyroscope and accelerometer measurements
\item
  Compare and evaluate all seven controllers on quadrotor hover and trajectory-tracking tasks using quantitative metrics (RMSE, computation time, wind rejection)
\end{itemize}

